snippet.textDisplay: University, the ideas great, choose course, wait and see if you get the entrance grades, get a big loan in the assumption your going to be taught a new skill. The reality is however somewhat different. Most teachers,lecturers including those with fancy titles have no qualification in teaching. Then theres the fact that generally and amazingly they actualy talk a lot and give you projects to complete  but dont actualy teach you a thing. Your left to find it all out yourself and provide the answers and expected to comply. Fail to comply e.g.  keep up with the work and pass the exams and your out. Then add the fact that many of these so called teachers treat these students who are paying a shit load of money for there degrees like children, wtf your paying to be there they work for you. And then the final reward you get your degree based on personal research and next to no real teaching have upto a 70k debt and no real skills for the job you just secured, But who cares you must be ideal for the position as you have a degree. What a joke. Keep at it it's all smoke and mirrors and I have no doubt you  will secure some fantastic job paying you 100k + per year. :) but dont believe the crap. And as far as the coronovirus its about time these educational establishments start thinking about the health of there customers and send you all home. They wont until there told as they are motivated by money! So dont be puppets and decide yourselves.
